    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1924-01-21T07:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1924-01-21T07:00:00-05:00" n="166"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d166">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.2300/27: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Austria</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Washburn</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Vienna</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1924-01-21T13:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 21, 1924—1 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received January 22—7:07 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3. Department’s telegram 3, January 18, 7 a.m. [<hi rend="italic">p.m.</hi>]<note
                        n="97" xml:id="d166fn97">Not printed.</note> Foreign Office states that
                    requests made by Legation in pursuance of Department’s telegram 23, December 22,
                    3 p.m.,<note n="98" xml:id="d166fn98">See footnote 92, <ref target="#pg_232">p.
                            232</ref>.</note> will be granted and that written reply to Legation’s
                    note will be forthcoming without delay.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washburn</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
